args:
After the party rescues the believers from an
assassin named Alex, Elisanne explains a split
in the Church that arose from a dispute over
something called the Scrolls of Perdition.
The party then pursues Alex into the volcano
to stop her from claiming any more victims.
Okay, we're at the church.\nAre the survivors all right?
Hear me, good people! I am the\nPaladyn Elisanne, and we have\ncome to answer your call for aid!
Lady Elisanne? THE Lady Elisanne?!\nShe's really here?!
Oh, wonder of wonders, we're saved!
Hmph. You are saved from nothing.
What the...?! No! Who are you?!
You have my gratitude for leading me\nhere, Elisanne. It made my job of finding\nthese fugitives considerably easier.
All the creatures of this earth are\nmy eyes and ears. My divine punishment\nis inescapable...and will be your end.
If you would invite hope into your heart,\nyou also invite despair along with it.
Alex! It WAS you who attacked Valkaheim!
Hey, why does that lady seem familiar?
Oh, WAIT! She's the chick from the woods!\nFrom when we first met Elisanne!
Would you PLEASE listen?\nI have no quarrel with you!
I care not. Now hold still\nand prepare to die.
You're the assassin that was chasing Elly!
The hell's your damn problem?!\nThese folks didn't do nothin' wrong,\nand yer tryin' to kill 'em like fiends!
...Nothing wrong? Do you actually believe\nthese people to be true adherents of Ilia?
Hear me well: These people are traitors\nwho trample upon the goddess's teachings!
And your dear comrade Elisanne\nis no Paladyn at all!
She has cast aside both her goddess\nand her faith! She is a breaker of vows,\nand I name her heretic!
Bullcrap! If you keep wagging your tongue\nlike that, I'm gonna nail it to the wall!
Ah, but is a Paladyn's duty not to protect\nthe bishop and believers of the Church?
Yet this one has abandoned her duty to\ncast her lot with you! There can be no\nclearer proof of my words than this.
Make no mistake, I am a servant of the\ngoddess—her right hand here on earth—\nand I SHALL see her will executed!
By my blade, Elisanne, will you know\nIlia's final love. Now DIIIE!
How did you parry that blow?!
...No, it matters not. If you would defy the\ngoddess's judgment, traitorous prince,\nthen you shall share in Elisanne's fate.
Lady? I ain't much for math, but I'm\npretty damn sure we got ya outnumbered.
Oh, I recognize my disadvantage, sir.\nThat is why I shall finish you all off\none by one at a time of my choosing.
For now, I must deal with those lingering\nin the depths of these tunnels. Farewell!
Hey, Elly? I don't wanna be a nosy Notte,\nbut what's with all that junk she said\nabout betraying the bishop or whatever?
I had hoped to never speak of these\nthings to all of you.
Do you know anything about a rift within\nthe Ilian Church? Or have you ever heard\nof the Scrolls of Perdition?
No on both counts, I'm afraid.\nWhy don't you fill us in?
Okay, hang on. Yer sayin' these things—\nthese Scrolls of Perdition—claim that\nthe evil god Morsayati is Ilia's KID?!
That is exactly what the scrolls claim.\nAnd were there any truth to this,\nit would be the ruin of the Church.
Thankfully, the documents are clearly\nfalse. Yet even so, there are many\nwho chose to believe them.
This has led to a split in the Church\nbetween those who believe the veracity\nof the scrolls and those who deny it.
As a believer of the Church, it shames me\nto see how many people accept this\nobvious fabrication.
This is what led me to leave the Church—\nan act that subsequently caused Alex to\nname me a heretic.
But before she could kill you, you were\nsaved by {player_name}, yeah?
I'm super glad to hear you're a Paladyn\nand not some kind of Pala-DON'T!\n...Point for Notte! Zing!
I know I said the scrolls were lies,\nand yet they also contain an element\nthat I find...difficult to ignore.
They are affixed with the seal of the\narchbishop from that time—which is one\nreason so many believe them to be true.
Do you think there's some connection\nbetween the unrest in Valkaheim and\nthese Scrolls of Perdition?
I don't know. The Church has known peace\nfor ages now, yet suddenly Alex has struck.
Something may have happened.\nSomething big, that has upset\nthe Church's balance.
Well, we won't know the truth of all this\nuntil we can make our way to Valkaheim.
For the moment, though, let's get the\nsurvivors to safety.
Actually, m'lord, this isn't all of us.
There are several people who took\nrefuge deeper within the Forsaken Way.
What kinda idiot goes DEEPER\ninto this hellhole?!
They were bewitched by a dark haze that\npoured forth from the tunnel depths.
They walked inside as though under\na spell, their minds no longer their own.
Oh? Well, THAT is a piece of bad news.
Do you know what's happening, Mym?
I've sensed a VERY strange vibe in these\nmusty old tunnels since we first entered.
We heard they abandoned this place when\nit was overrun by lava...but that may not\nhave been the only reason.
You think there is some sinister force\nwaiting down in the depths?
Don't you remember what that Alex\nlady said earlier?!
She said she was gonna ＂deal with＂ some\npeople in the depths of the tunnels!
There's so much going on at the moment,\nit must have slipped right past me...
Right. Come on, everyone!\nWe have to go save those people!
